quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  7,196,"My guardian is indeed Allah who sent down the Book, and He takes care of the righteous"
  7,197,"Those whom you invoke besides Him can neither help you, nor help themselves"
  7,198,"If you call them to guidance, they will not hear. You see them facing you, but they do not see.’"
  7,199,"Adopt [a policy of] excusing [the faults of people], bid what is right, and turn away from the ignorant"
  7,200,"Should a temptation from Satan disturb you, invoke the protection of Allah; indeed He is all-hearing, all-knowing"
  7,201,"When those who are Godwary are touched by a visitation of Satan, they remember [Allah] and, behold, they perceive"
  7,202,"But their brethren, they draw them into error, and then they do not spare [any harm]"
  7,203,"When you do not bring them a sign, they say, ‘Why do you not improvise one?’ Say, ‘I only follow what is revealed to me from my Lord; these are insights from your Lord, and a guidance and mercy for a people who have faith.’"
  7,204,"When the Quran is recited, listen to it and be silent, maybe you will receive [Allah’s] mercy"
  7,205,"And remember your Lord within your heart beseechingly and reverentially, without being loud, morning, and evening, and do not be among the heedless"
  7,206,"Indeed those who are [stationed] near your Lord do not disdain to worship Him. They glorify Him and prostrate to Him"